Newcastle disease in Israel
-----------------------
See also: 17 Jun 2005, 20 May 2005, 15 Apr 2005
(Date of previous outbreak of Newcastle disease in Israel reported to the
OIE: May 2005).
Immediate notification report
Information received on 24 Jul 2005 from Dr Moshe Chaimovitz, Director of
Veterinary and Animal Health Services, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural
Development, Beit-Dagan:
Report date: 24 Jul 2005.
Reason for immediate notification: re-occurrence of a listed disease or
infection in a country or zone/compartment following a report declaring the
outbreak ended.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 17 Jul 2005.
Date of start of the event: 13 Jul 2005.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, post-mortem and laboratory.
Details of outbreak:
First administrative division: Acco
Lower administrative division: ...
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: peqi'in Hadasha
Species: avi
Number of animals in the outbreak
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
8000 / 60 / 50 / 7950 / 0
Description of affected population: 2 flock units of table egg layers were
affected.
Diagnosis:
1. Laboratories where diagnosis was made: Tsfat regional poultry disease
laboratory
Diagnostic tests used: ...
Date ...
Results ...
2. Laboratories where diagnosis was made: Kimron Veterinary Institute
Diagnostic tests used: haemagglutination inhibition test
Date ...
Results ...
Diagnostic tests used: pathogen isolation by egg inoculation
Date: 17 Jul 2005
Results: positive
Diagnostic tests used: PCR(1)
Date: 19 Jul 2005
Results: positive
Diagnostic tests used: intracerebral pathogenicity index (ICPI) test
Date: in progress
Results: pending
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measures undertaken:
- the flock was destroyed on 22 Jul 2005;
- all poultry holdings in the 3 villages within a radius of 3 km of the
outbreak were checked serologically and/or clinically for Newcastle disease;
- orders were issued to the owners of all poultry and other avian species
within a radius of 10 km to perform an immediate booster vaccination (using
live vaccine by spray -- VH strain ICPI 0.15);
- disinfection of infected premises;
- movement control inside the country.
Vaccination prohibited: no. Newcastle vaccination is compulsory in Israel.
(1) PCR: polymerase chain reaction
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Please note that this occurrence affects commercial poultry, not hobby
birds, as in the 2 previous reports referenced below. - Mod.PC]
